<application>
	<id type="desktop">mediawriter.desktop</id>
	<project_license>GPL-2.0+</project_license>
	<metadata_license>CC0-1.0</metadata_license>
	<name>ALT Media Writer</name>
	<summary>A tool to create a live USB drive with an edition of ALT</summary>
	<description>
		<p>A tool to create a bootable live USB drive with an edition of ALT. Not only can ALT Media Writer write an image to your flash drive, it can also download it for you. It offers official editions (Workstation, Education, Server), ALT starterkits (KDE Plasma Desktop, Xfce Desktop, Cinnamon Desktop,...), and ALT regulars (Rescue, Builder,...). It provides basic information about each of them to help you make the right choice.</p>
		<p>ALT Media Writer can also write other bootable ISOs loaded from your local disk, but keep in mind that it's only tested with ALT images.</p>
	</description>
